---
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PhotographyGallery from '../../components/projects/PhotographyGallery.astro';
import Lightbox from '../../components/projects/Lightbox.astro';

const all = await getCollection('projects');
const photography = all.filter((p) => p.data.kind === 'photography');
---

<BaseLayout
  title="To See, and to See Again."
  description="One photograph a day by Pranika Jain, and one taken by a stranger with her camera in the same place."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-page px-5 py-16 sm:px-8 sm:py-24">
    <a
      href="/projects"
      class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 font-sans text-sm text-terracotta-600 underline-offset-4 hover:underline dark:text-terracotta-300"
      >&larr; All projects</a
    >

    <header class="mt-6 mb-12">
      <p
        class="flex items-center gap-3 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-terracotta-600 dark:text-terracotta-300"
      >
        <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" aria-hidden="true" class="h-3.5 w-3.5">
          <circle
            cx="8"
            cy="8"
            r="6"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="1.6"></circle>
          <circle cx="8" cy="8" r="2" fill="currentColor"></circle>
        </svg>
        To See, and to See Again
      </p>
      <h1
        class="mt-3 font-display text-4xl leading-tight tracking-tight text-ink sm:text-5xl dark:text-cream"
      >
        To See, and to See <span class="italic">Again</span>.
      </h1>
      <p
        class="mt-5 font-sans text-lg text-ink-soft dark:text-cream-soft"
      >
        Lately I've started carrying a camera. I'm a few days into a habit of taking one photograph a day, and asking a stranger to take one with my camera too, when I can. I was curious to know what two people see in the same place at the same time. Most days the photos aren't much. Once in a while one of them won't leave me alone.
      </p>
       <p
        class="mt-5 font-sans text-lg text-ink-soft dark:text-cream-soft"
      > 
       I also ask each stranger for a word, or a sentence. Sometimes they look at the photo again before answering, and find something they hadn't seen when they raised the camera.
      </p>
    </header>

    <PhotographyGallery entries={photography} />

    <Lightbox />
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
